# **Seal Skip**

The&nbsp;**Seal Skip**&nbsp;can be used to skip getting the&nbsp;[Key to the Seal](https://darksouls.wikidot.com/key-to-the-seal)&nbsp;from Ingward and lowering the water in [New Londo Ruins](http://darksouls.wikidot.com/new-londo-ruins) by using a&nbsp;quit-out&nbsp;and&nbsp;[Fall Control](https://darksouls.wikidot.com/fall-control)&nbsp;to get to the [Four Kings](http://darksouls.wikidot.com/the-four-kings). It was discovered by Fed981 in December 2014 on PTDE version of the game.\
It is possible to perform it without Fall Control, though the timing is more precise. From there it is possible to fall into the Abyss via an OoB path.

This skip is not allowed in [Glitchless categories](/ds1remaster/glitchless) of the game.

## **External Resources**

- Medium difficulty & consistent seal skip tutorial without Fall Control [https://youtu.be/v-Jl1E6xx1E](https://youtu.be/v-Jl1E6xx1E)  by m3dic on YouTube.
- Classic seal skip demonstration without Fall Control ( a bit more faster but very complicated) [https://youtu.be/X2NwsNKbLY0?t=1196](https://youtu.be/X2NwsNKbLY0?t=1196)  by aeiou on YouTube.
